review_blob: Bottle. Pours a slightly hazy orange with a white head that settles slowly, thin lacing. Aroma is hoppy, resinous, bitter, and oily. Flavor is hoppy, moderately bitter, piney, with a very mild malt background. Bitter, very slightly soapy finish. Soft to moderate carbonation. Perfect well balanced IPA

Pours a reddish orange pour with a small head. Aroma is sweet citrusl. Taste is very bigwith hops mostly citrus to me, and very drinkable. which I would never have guessed would be so low. Finish is dry and ends on sweet citrus notes. This is my new favorite beer. I really believe this should get a lot hire score then 94

Poured from the bottle. Pours deal rich ruby red/brown in color. Softy carbonation with plenty of head. Taste is very earthy and well balanced.  One of of the best wild ales I have had in a very long time

Pours malty black with a perfect head to it. Smells of sherry and oak and rum. The taste is so complex with so may different levels of taste.  This is one of the most original stouts I have a had in a long time.  It time this can be known as one of the best beers in the world

Bright golden color,small soft white head.Malty sweet aroma with a medium hop presence mild citrus and a spicy hint.The taste is grapefruit and hops with an almost buttery feel.It is sweet upfront the changes to a subtle hop bitter in the end. This is a great drink everyday pale ale
